<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-06 12:03 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0569 &Cx1f; tad-z
u k BC-JOEMURRAY-COLUMN07-CO     12-06 0623
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-JOEMURRAY-COLUMN07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    TALL TALES &AMP; SHORT STORIES: Windows into paradise
 &HT;    (Eds: Eighth in a series from Paris. Photo available by calling
404-526-5456.)
 &HT;    By Joe Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AIX-EN-PROVENCE, France _ If you're traveling in a foreign
country and planning to stay in a remote bed-and-breakfast, it's a
good idea to take a look at the rooms before making a commitment.
</P>
<P>
   No problem at La Campagne Jeanne. You can look even before
making the trip.
</P>
<P>
   Thanks to the Internet, it's possible to take a Web-site tour of
the home of Martine and Daniel Alexandrian, which they opened to
the public as a B&AMP;B in May 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Online, www.campagne-jeanne.com features text and photos
detailing rooms, decor, bathroom facilities, meals and recipes,
plus views of the countryside where you'll be staying.
</P>
<P>
   That's Daniel's contribution to the enterprise, thanks to his
expertise in computers. Martine takes it from there, doing all the
cooking and cleaning herself for as many as six guests at a time.
</P>
<P>
   It's what she always wanted, said Daniel, who speaks English and
translates for his wife.
</P>
<P>
   ``She dreamed of having her own bed and breakfast for a long,
long time,'' he said, ``and it has all come true.''
</P>
<P>
   Daniel and Martine _ now in their middle to late 40s and with
two grown children _ invested in a couple of acres of fields in the
countryside some three miles from the city of Aix-en-Provence,
restored a pair of century-old farmhouses and joined them together
with a new structure of stone, stucco and antique timbers in
keeping with the old style of Provence.
</P>
<P>
   One other thing they added that was very much new for B&AMP;Bs in
rural France: a site on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   Has it been successful?
</P>
<P>
   ``Very good,'' Daniel said, laughing. ``Exceptional ...
unbelievable. ... Sometimes we could have rented the rooms two or
three times over.''
</P>
<P>
   Successful to the point that 80 to 90 percent of their business
comes from the Web, mostly from people in the U.S. and other
countries where use of the Internet is commonplace.
</P>
<P>
   But not so much in France.
</P>
<P>
   ``The French make it a habit to call just the day they are
coming,'' Daniel said. ``As a result, they often find that no rooms
are available.''
</P>
<P>
   So it is that La Campagne Jeanne has cast a wide net, attracting
visitors from South Africa, Australia, Brazil and India.
</P>
<P>
   But it may be Martine who keeps them coming back, and staying
longer.
</P>
<P>
   A room for two costs $40 to $60, including breakfast. For an
extra $20 per person, you get dinner. Martine serves as chef,
specializing in traditional dishes of Provence.
</P>
<P>
   A few of her favorites: Anchoiade, barigoule, grilled sweet
pepper salad, stuffed sardines, pistou soup, Provencal tomatoes.
Recipes are included on the Web site.
</P>
<P>
   Daniel, who works in Aix, pop. 150,000, for a company dealing in
environmental issues, said that operating the B&AMP;B has been an
enjoyable experience.
</P>
<P>
   ``People who come looking for this kind of accommodation are
looking for something different, and maybe they are different
themselves,'' he said. ``One French couple stayed two months. By
the time they left, it was like losing old friends.''
</P>
<P>
   Next year, Daniel and Martine hope to add an extra room and,
perhaps in three years, yet another one, for a maximum of 10
guests.
</P>
<P>
   Such is Martine's dream - along with one other thing.
</P>
<P>
   ``By then,'' Daniel said, ``she hopes we can also add some
staff.''
</P>
<P>
   (Joe Murray, editor-publisher emeritus of the Lufkin Daily News,
is senior writer of Cox Newspapers. Mailing address is P.O. Box
151108, Lufkin, Texas 75904; e-mail, jmurray(AT)lcc.net.)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
