<HEADER>
A0667 &Cx1f; tab-z
r l BC-CHRISTIAN-SEX-ADVICE-     12-06 1437
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CHRISTIAN-SEX-ADVICE-SLATE </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A GUIDE TO THE BOOMING CHRISTIAN SEX-ADVICE INDUSTRY 
</HEADLINE>
  (Slate commentary)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (To purchase this ``separate buy'' article from the New York
Times Syndicate please contact syndicate sales representative DEBRA
WEYDERT at 732-390-4480)
</P>
<P>
   (Mark Oppenheimer is writing a book about American religion and
the 1960s counterculture.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By MARK OPPENHEIMER &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   When University of Chicago researchers set out to discover which
religious denominations have the best sex, they learned that the
faithful don't do all their shouting in church.
</P>
<P>
   Conservative Protestant women, their 1994 survey found, report
