tug is particularly acute for Christians and Jews whose seasonal
celebrations collide head on with Christmas and Hanukkah. Many
families are now synthesizing the two customs, and the commercial
marketplace is starting to respond by producing what was once
taboo: decorations that merge the symbols of two observances. By
