<HEADLINE>
`INSPECTOR GADGET' JOINS `LIVE CARTOON' FAILURES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Inspector Gadget'' _ Ever since the success of
the live-action, big-screen ``George of the Jungle,'' producers
have tried to bring other cartoon characters to life. Leslie
Nielsen in ``Mr. Magoo'' bombed. Brendan Fraser in ``Dudley
Do-Right'' bombed. Now Matthew Broderick, in the least promising of
them all, bombs. The animated ``Inspector Gadget'' had one thing
going for it: Don Adams's voice. Adams, who played a live-action
``Gadget'' type on the vintage TV spy parody ``Get Smart,'' brought
that baggage with him to `Gadget.'' Broderick is left to fend for
himself, with too many gadgets and not enough script.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW ON DVD: Distributors are releasing about 50 new titles a
week on DVD. One of the best is ``The Iron Giant'' _ an animated
science-fiction film that's designed more for adult fans of the
genre than for children. References to '50s films abound, and the
story is a paean to ``E. T. The Extra-Terrestrial.'' Also, check
out Jonathan Demme's Talking Heads concert documentary, ``Stop
Making Sense.'' The sound quality is extraordinary. There are
several songs added that were cut from the theatrical release, plus
commentary by Talking Head David Byrne and talking head Demme. . .
. The Christmas shopping surge has warmed the commercial hearts of
DVD manufacturers, with sales of DVD players at a rate more than
double last year's.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Dec. 14: ``Buena Vista Social Club'' (DVD),
``Drop Dead Gorgeous,'' ``The Harmonists,'' ``The Red Violin''
(DVD), ``Teaching Mrs. Tingle,'' ``The Very Thought of You,'' ``A
Knight in Camelot.'' Dec. 21: ``Run Lola Run'' (DVD), ``American
Pie'' (DVD), ``Tampopo'' (DVD), ``Summer of Sam,'' ``Ethics for the
New Millennium,'' ``The Adventures of Elmo in Grouchland,'' ``A
Taxing Woman'' (DVD), ``The Funeral'' (DVD), ``K-911'' (DVD),
``Supercop 2,'' ``Witness to the Mob.'' Dec. 28: ``Dudley
Do-Right,'' ``Better Than Chocolate,'' ``Desert Blue'' (DVD). Jan.
4: ``The Thomas Crown Affair'' (DVD), ``Sayonara.'' Jan. 11: ``The
Art of Buster Keaton'' (DVD), ``The Extreme Adventures of Super
Dave.'' Jan. 18: ``An Ideal Husband,'' ``The Hitchhiker,'' ``From
Dusk to Dawn 3,'' ``The 13th Warrior.'' ``The Wood'' (DVD). Jan.
25: ``Runaway Bride,'' ``My Life So Far,'' ``The Sex Monster,''
``My Son the Fanatic,'' ``The Tempest,'' ``Woman Wanted.'' Feb. 1:
``The Cabinet of Dr. Caligari,'' ``Nosferatu.''
</P>
</TEXT>
