   That afternoon in the Seattle movie theater, Pikachu created a
mellow ambience. Unfortunately, that does not seem to be the
prevailing mood at the WTO meeting. &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (EDITOR'S NOTE: Yoichi Funabashi is an Asahi Shimbun senior staff
writer and foreign affairs columnist.) &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; ___________________ &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; (To publish this 775-word article from the Asahi News Service, it
must be purchased from the New York Times Syndicate's sales
representative DEBRA WEYDERT at 732-390-4480, or fax her at
732-390-4697. Her e-mail address is weyded(at)nytimes.com. If
unable to reach Ms. Weydert, please call 800-444-0267, or fax us at
816-822-1444.) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
