</P>
<P>
   TECH-GADGETS _ DAYTON, Ohio _ The SoundScience Universal Audio
Dynamic Sound Improvement Processor promises to ``enhance
reproduction for fuller, cleaner, undiluted sound with sharp
mid-tones, crisp trebles and powerful bass'' from your CD player,
television, computer, DVD player, radio, cassette player, satellite
receiver and video game consoles. But the real result is distorted
tones and low-quality sound. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News) MOVED
(f, l)
