<P>
   WEDNESDAY, Dec. 8
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-COST _ WASHINGTON _ As Al Gore and Hillary Rodham
Clinton pursue their political travels, taxpayers are footing most
of the bill. Just paying for their military airplanes costs more
than $4,000 an hour for her and $10,000 an hour for him. Campaign
reimbursements don't come close to the real cost and have ``always
been frankly ridiculous,'' said the head of one private watchdog
group. One escape: candidates using corporate jets, which also
brings controversy. And in the case of Gov. George W. Bush of
Texas, it's the increased cost of security that's raising
questions. (Malone).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   NOTES: In Taipei, 50th anniversary of the flight of Chinese
Nationalists from the Chinese mainland, moving their capital to
Formosa (Taiwan).
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY, Dec. 9
</P>
<P>
   FRIDAY, Dec. 10
</P>
<P>
   GORE-SOUTH _ WASHINGTON _ If Al Gore wins the Democratic
presidential nomination, it will be because of the South. The Old
Confederacy is his ace in the hole should he stumble in the early
voting in Iowa and New Hampshire. As a consequence, he rarely lets
a week pass without tending to his Southern political supporters _
and especially African Americans. For example, he'll be in Atlanta
this weekend for a meeting with black voters before heading to
Orlando for the Florida state Democratic convention. (Shepard).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Gore is scheduled to visit Georgia and Florida beginning
Dec. 10.
</P>
<P>
   DIGITAL-DIVIDE _ WASHINGTON _ Corporate chief executives join
Commerce Secretary William M. Daley at a ``Digital Divide''
conference to examine public and private initiatives aimed at
closing the technology gap between rich and poor. (Glass).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY, Dec. 11
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-EXTREMISTS-$ADV11 _ JERUSALEM _ How nervous are they?
Well, the Israeli police commander has forbidden his officers from
giving interviews about their preparations for the millennium.
What's known is that surveillance cameras are being placed on holy
sites and extra police are being posted. Police have already
deported foreigners believed to be a little too fervent about the
end of time. Also, the head of a Jerusalem mental ward expects
extra cases of the so-called ``Jerusalem Syndrome.'' (Kaplow).
</P>
<P>
   With Photos.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in International/Lifestyle categories.
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-MILLENIUM-$ADV11 _ LONDON _ London wants to be center of
the universe for the upcoming millennium celebration, spending
millions in money, marketing and man-hours to make that happen. We
give a more detailed account of what to expect here. Developing.
(Emling, Special to the Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   With a list of what London is offering for those bitten by the
Millenium bug.
</P>
<P>
   With photos.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in International/Lifestyle/Travel categories.
