   MONDAY, Dec. 13
</P>
<P>
   (New date) MEAT-HACCP _ WASHINGTON _ The Agriculture
Department's new science-based food safety inspection program is
running into the same problem as the ``poke and sniff'' program it
replaced: federal officials take no action against meat and poultry
plants that amass hundreds of violations. And an examination of the
government's own records also found that in some parts of the
country over 20 percent of the scheduled federal inspections are
never done because of manpower shortages. (Montgomery and Jaspin).
</P>
<P>
   NOTES: The Panama Canal Transfer Commemorative Ceremonies are
held over the next two days. Williams covering.
