<P>
   MEXICO-MILLENNIUM-$ADV18 _ MEXICO CITY _ As the new millennium
approaches, what affect is it having on this country of devout
Catholics? What preparations are being made by folks here in terms
of a celebration? Developing. (Ferriss).
</P>
<P>
   With Photos.
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-TRAVEL-$ADV18 _ A review of what's going on at the
millennium sites. At Armageddon, the place where the battle to end
all battles is supposed to occur, the Israelis have fixed up the
park that is there. At the Church of the Holy Sepulchre, where
orthodox Christians believe Christ was crucified, the five
bickering denominations in charge are trying to agree on where to
place an exit door _ the first change in the church in years. In
Bethlehem, the Palestinians have rebuilt the plaza and torn down
the ugly old British jail next to the church. (Kaplow).
</P>
<P>
   With MIDEAST-TRAVELAGENTS-$ADV18 _ JERUSALEM _ It took the
millennium to make it happen, but for the first time Israelis and
Palestinians have formed a travel agency together. They hope to
cash in on a boom of tourists that has so far prompted mostly
bitter and unproductive competition between the two sides.
Generally, Israelis are trying to steer tourists to their Christian
sites and hotels, and the Palestinians are trying to do the same.
(Kaplow).
</P>
<P>
   With photos.
</P>
