</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-ELECTIONS-$ADV19 _ MOSCOW _ An advancer setting up the
Russian parliamentary elections on Sunday. Developing. (Holmes).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in both International/Commentary categories.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RETURNEE-$ADV19 _ We interview Skender Rahimi and his
family. Rahimi is a Kosovo Albanian refugee who went to the United
States, but then returned to Kosovo after the NATO bombing
campaign. (Roughton).
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-MACAU-$ADV19_ MACAU - The checkered history of this
indolent old Portuguese enclave is about to end, and few are
weeping as the China prepares to take over. Four hundred years ago
Macau was far richer. Portuguese traders dined on plates of gold
because for a century Portugal had a world monopoly on trade in
silk, gold, porcelain and silver with Japan and China. Twelve years
ago, China and Portugal had no trouble agreeing that the Portuguese
should end their occupation just before the millennium. Both sides
have stuck to this pact with little friction. And so on the evening
of December 19, 2,500 guests from Portugal, Macau and China are due
to gather here just before midnight to toast the end of nearly 450
years of Portuguese occupation. When the clock in the Macau
cathedral strikes 12 times, Portugal will lower its flag on the
last and oldest Western enclave in Asia. (Kunstel/Albright).
</P>
<P>
   With MACAU-BOX-$ADV19 _ Vital statistics and/or timeline on
Macao. (Kunstel/Albright).
</P>
<P>
   With Photos.
</P>
