<P>
   KARENNA-GORE _ NEW YORK _ Rarely has a child of a presidential
candidate played such an integral part in a campaign as Karenna
Gore Schiff, the eldest child of Vice President Al Gore. She
introduced her father at his official announcement of his candidacy
and, a month later, made him a grandfather with perfect timing,
giving birth to her son on the Fourth of July. But Karenna is not
just a surrogate for her father on the campaign trail, the way most
candidates's children have been. She is deeply involved in GoreNet,
his cyber-campaign aimed at young voters. (Shepard).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (p) politics and (l) lifestyle categories.
