<HEADLINE>
RUSSIAN TEXT OF LEAFLET WARNING RESIDENTS TO LEAVE GROZNY 
</HEADLINE>
  (With Chechnya-Russia) 
(jt) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here is the text of a leaflet to civilians dropped by Russian
forces on Monday on Grozny, the besieged Chechen capital, as
translated by The New York Times.
</P>
<P>
   Residents of the city of Grozny! Russian troops are completing
the encirclement of the city. In order to avoid civilian
casualties, we propose that you leave the city of Grozny before
December 11, 1999. Use any means possible. The Command of the
Combined Group of Russian Forces has set up a checkpoint for
civilians in Pervomayskoye, and a tent camp has been set up so you
can settle in Znamenskoye. You are guaranteed all constitutional
rights. After the completion of the counter-terrorism operation you
will be able to return to your homes. Do not give in to the
provocations of the terrorists and the bandits. Do not allow them
to use you for their purposes. Only in this way will you be able to
avoid death and save your city. Remember, preservation of life and
the provision of security for the civilian population is the main
task of the Russian troops.
</P>
</TEXT>
