<P>
   HEART-SURGERY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Irvin Knudson was alert, even after two heart attacks.
But he was also 92 years old. Twice, Dr. Manucher Nazarian refused
to do the surgery. The ethics committee at Harris Methodist Fort
Worth also discussed the case. Finally, Nazarian tried what he
considered Knudson's only surgical option, a double bypass
performed while Knudson's heart was still beating. Nazarian is
considered one of the local pioneers of the innovative and still
somewhat controversial surgery, which avoids the use of a
heart-lung machine. Two weeks ago, Knudson and his 85-year-old wife
returned to their Eastside home, where he hopes to soon be back in
his garden. By CHARLOTTE HUFF. Story will move in ``a'' general
news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   L I F E S T Y L E &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   POTTER-ESSAY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Harry Potter, the kid-lit protagonist, and Pokmon are
taking a beating these days. Kids, obviously, love them, but mobs
of vocal adults question whether the pop phenoms are actually,
well, evil. One mom sounds off in defense of these modern-day fairy
tales. By CATHERINE NEWTON. Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
