<P>
   (NYT30) TOKYO -- Dec. 6, 1999 -- TOKYO EXAM OBSESSION, --
Yoshiko Otsuka teaches a three-year old girl in a class at the
Cecillia Pre-School Center in Tokyo's Bunkyo Ward on Monday. At
first glance, there is very little to distinguish the scene here
from an ordinary nursery school in other countries. But just as
surely as the students come to this special preparatory school once
a week from their ordinary nursery schools for an intensive burst
of one-on-one learning with teachers, they are taking their first
step into the country's performance-obsessed national school
examination system.(Stuart Isett/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
