<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    What they said: A sampling of quotes from Monday Night's GOP
debate
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ON EDUCATION
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't believe in national testing. I believe local folks
ought to develop their own tests and standards.'' _ Gov. George W.
Bush on local control
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think this is a gun problem. I think it's a problem of
the heart and soul.'' _ Gary Bauer on school violence
</P>
<P>
   ``The best thing we can do is provide a means for kids in the
inner city who aren't getting a good education _ and parents know
they're not getting a good education _ to walk.'' _ Sen. Orrin
Hatch on school vouchers
</P>
<P>
   ``We need to test vouchers, we don't need to take the money from
public education.'' _ Sen. John McCain on school vouchers
</P>
<P>
   ``Once we took prayer out, we seemed to let violence and decline
in.'' _ Alan Keyes on school violence
</P>
<P>
   ``The real way you give parents freedom is first let them keep
more of what they earn in the first place.'' _ Steve Forbes on the
connection between taxes and school vouchers
</P>
<P>
   ON TAXATION AND THE ECONOMY
</P>
<P>
   ``The prosperity we're enjoying today...those foundations were
laid by Ronal Reagan in the early 1980s.'' _ Forbes
</P>
<P>
   ``If you can't afford to be heavily taxed right now, you will
confine yourself to goods that aren't taxed.'' _ Keyes on a
national sales tax
</P>
<P>
   ``There are terrible inequities in the tax code.'' _ McCain
</P>
<P>
   ``It's important for the Republican Party and the Republican
nominee to hear the cry of people on the outskirts of poverty.'' _
Bush
</P>
<P>
   ON FOREIGN POLICY
</P>
<P>
   ``Even rich and powerful countries like the United States will
be bled dry if we intervene everywhere our hearts have been
touched.'' _ Bauer
</P>
<P>
   ``This (Clinton) administration is poll driven and not principle
driven. This administration has conducted a feckless photo op on
foreign policy for which we'll pay a very high price in blood and
treasure.'' _ McCain
</P>
<P>
   ``This throwing our forces around, and then not having an exit
strategy and not building up our military is a policy for
disaster.'' _ Forbes
</P>
<P>
   ``I think if we turn our back on China and isolate China, things
will get worse.'' _ Bush
</P>
